it.unipr.netsec.nemo.examples

Class FilteringRouter

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unipr.netsec.ipstack.net.Node
      • it.unipr.netsec.ipstack.ip4.Ip4Node
        • it.unipr.netsec.nemo.ip.Ip4Router
          • it.unipr.netsec.nemo.examples.FilteringRouter

  • public class FilteringRouter
extends Ip4Router
    Example of an IPv4 packet filtering router.

    It filters packets based on their destination addresses. It may work with either an ACCEPT or DROP default policy.

    If the default policy is ACCEPT then the filter rules in the ACL specify the target addresses to be dropped. If the default policy is DROP then the filter rules specify the target addresses to be accepted.
